e County","state":"New York","country":"United States","zip":"14620","gps":{"latitude":43.1297,"longitude":-77.6201},"founded":1838,"visitable":true,"notes":"One of America's oldest municipal Victorian cemeteries (founded 1838 — pre-dating the famous Mt. Auburn). The Gordon family plot is in Lot 61 Range 2 — purchased by Luther Gordon Sr. (Brockport bank founder, 1818-1881). His son George Cooley Gordon Sr. (X02281, NOTABLE) paid $9,229.54 for perpetual care of the plot in 1883. The plot features a stunning monument with columns and an allegorical female figure with drapery, one hand across her heart and the other holding a cross, gazing into the distance. Modest stones below in a square perimeter — except for infant William 'Willie' Gordon's stone (HD3268, 1879-1880) prominently set below the central angel monument. Hooker-line burials at Mt. Hope: George Cooley Gordon Sr (X02281), Ida May Hooker Gordon (H03892, with monument), William 'Willie' Gordon (HD3268), George Cooley Gordon II (HD3262), Cecelia Mitchell Kimball Gordon (X02282), George Cooley Gordon III (HD3263), Cornelia Macy Hawks Gordon (X02283), Cecilia 'Trottie' Gordon (HD3264), Laura Kimball Gordon (HD3265), Fred Hooker Gordon Sr (HD3266) with separate Section MM Lot 266 plot, Florence Robinson Gordon (X02284), Fred Hooker Gordon Jr (HD-prefix), Virginia DeVilbiss Gordon (X-prefix), Fred Hooker Gordon III (HD-prefix, infant Boston meningioma), Lucius Robinson 'Bob' Gordon (HD-prefix, NOTABLE), Marie Antoinette 'Tony' Townson Gordon (X-prefix), William Ward Gordon (HD-prefix), Emilie Wolcott Gordon (X-prefix), William Ward Gordon Jr (HD-prefix back in original Lot 61 Range 2). Largest Hooker-tree concentration after Cypress Lawn SF.","hooker_connections":["H03434","H03437","H03892","HD3261","HD3262","HD3263","HD3264","HD3265","HD3266","HD3267","HD3268","HD3275","HD3276","HD3277","HD3279","HD3280","HD3400","HD3401","HD3834","HD3836","HD3842","I00339","X02281","X02282","X02283","X02284","X02290","X02293",